<emphasis box="[151,241,1999,2023]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Olidiana</emphasis>
<treatmentCitation author="McKamey, S. H." box="[248,459,1998,2023]" page="503" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" year="2006">
<bibRefCitation author="McKamey, S. H." box="[248,459,1998,2023]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="502 - 510" refId="ref38427" refString="McKamey, S. H. (2006) Further new genus-group names in the Cicadellidae (Hemiptera). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 108 (3), 502 - 510." type="journal article" year="2006">Mckamey 2006: 503</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, new name for 
<taxonomicName authority="Nielson 1982: 86 - 87" authorityName="Nielson" authorityPageNumber="86" authorityYear="1982" box="[616,923,1998,2023]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Lodiana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[616,700,1999,2023]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Lodiana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Nielson, M. W." box="[706,923,1998,2023]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 318" refId="ref38619" refString="Nielson, M. W. (1982) A revision of the subfamily Coelidiinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae) IV. Coelidiini. Pacific Insects Monograph, 38, 1 - 318." type="journal article" year="1982">Nielson 1982: 86−87</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, not Ragonot 1888; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nielson, M. W." box="[1128,1345,1998,2023]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 202" refId="ref38859" refString="Nielson, M. W. (2015) A revision of the tribe Coelidiini of the Oriental, Palearctic and Australian biogeographical regions (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae: Coelidiinae). Insecta Mundi, 0410, 1 - 202." type="book chapter" year="2015">Nielson 2015: 35−36</bibRefCitation>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,265,154,179]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nielson." authorityYear="1982" box="[405,495,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Calodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[405,495,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Calodia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in general habitus. Pygofer in lateral view triangular, longer than height, without prominent caudodorsal process but with small lobe apically, often with caudoventral process. Subgenital plate glabrous to setose. Style variable. Aedeagus long, narrow, tubular with one short to long subapical process, setose and/or spinose process, sometimes with small teeth or setae near or adjacent to subapical process.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,153,323]" box="[199,1218,297,323]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">The genus includes 83 species in the Old World including four new species described here.</paragraph>
